</pre>
<p>A <a href="/wiki/Suffix_tree" title="Suffix tree">suffix tree</a> for a string is a <a href="/wiki/Trie" title="Trie">trie</a> <a href="/wiki/Data_structure" title="Data structure">data structure</a> that represents all of its suffixes. Suffix trees have large numbers of applications in <a href="/wiki/String_(computer_science)#String_processing_algorithms" title="String (computer science)">string algorithms</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Suffix_array" title="Suffix array">suffix array</a> is a simplified version of this data structure that lists the start positions of the suffixes in alphabetically sorted order; it has many of the same applications.
</p>
